Politics.headline: Trump Imposes New Tariffs, Denounces Supreme Court Justices After Ruling
Politics.detail: Following a Supreme Court ruling against his previous tariffs, President Trump announced new global tariffs and criticized the justices involved.

Politics.headline: India signs critical minerals deal with Brazil to curb dependance on China
Politics.detail: Brazilian President Lula called the critical minerals and rare earths deal the 'core of the pioneering agreement'.

Politics.headline: Ahead of budget bill vote, veterans plead with Ottawa to change course
Politics.detail: Veterans and their advocates are urging the Carney Liberals to amend a bill before the House of Commons to remove sections that they say unfairly target people who served Canada.

Politics.headline: Clashes in Albania as protesters demand PM Rama resign
Politics.detail: Protests have erupted in Albania as demonstrators demand the resignation of Prime Minister Rama.

Politics.headline: UK weighs removing ex-Prince Andrew from succession line amid Epstein probe.
Politics.detail: The UK is considering removing ex-Prince Andrew from the line of succession amidst the ongoing Epstein probe.

Finance & Economy.headline: Trump Announces New Blanket Tariff After Supreme Court Ruling
Finance & Economy.detail: Following a Supreme Court decision that struck down his previous tariff policies, President Trump announced a new 10% tariff on all imports from every country, effective almost immediately. The move signals a major shift in US trade policy.

Finance & Economy.headline: US Supreme Court Strikes Down Trump's Global Tariffs
Finance & Economy.detail: In a 6-3 decision, the Supreme Court invalidated a large portion of President Trump's tariffs, ruling that the executive branch exceeded its authority under the International Emergency Economic Powers Act. The ruling raises questions for businesses, consumers, and global markets, potentially leading to refunds of over $175 billion in collected tariffs.

Finance & Economy.headline: UK 'Working with US' to Analyse Impact of Court Ruling Against Tariffs
Finance & Economy.detail: Following the US Supreme Court's ruling against President Trump's tariffs, the UK government is collaborating with the US to analyze the potential impact. The decision has been welcomed as a win for world trade but also presents tricky implications.

Finance & Economy.headline: Economists Analyze Impact of Bank Regulatory Reform on Economic Growth
Finance & Economy.detail: According to a model developed by Fed economists, reforms enacted in 2025 to make banking regulations more transparent and risk-reflective are projected to boost GDP by over 0.5% by the end of 2026. Bank loans to businesses and households grew 5.5% in 2025, a notable increase from the previous two years.

Finance & Economy.headline: Stock Market Experts Weigh In on Market Outlook Following Tech Sell-Off
Finance & Economy.detail: Following a turbulent period for some stock market investors and a tech sell-off, analysts offer mixed opinions on the S&P 500's trajectory, with some anticipating a continued upward trend and others expressing concerns about a wider correction. The FTSE 100, with limited exposure to the tech sector, is predicted to have a strong year, supported by increasing dividend payments.

Technology.headline: OpenAI Smart Speaker Can Allow You to Buy Things Through Facial Recognition
Technology.detail: OpenAI is reportedly developing a camera-equipped, screen-free AI speaker with Jony Ive, aiming to launch in 2027 as a proactive smart home rival to Apple.

Technology.headline: Artificial intelligence catches over 4000 fraudulent student applications at El Camino College
Technology.detail: LightLeap AI software has significantly decreased fraudulent enrollment by identifying over 4,000 spring 2026 applications as fraudulent, improving the accuracy of El Camino College's enrollment numbers.

Technology.headline: PM participates in the groundbreaking ceremony of HCL-Foxconn Semiconductor Unit in Uttar Pradesh via Video Conferencing
Technology.detail: Prime Minister Modi participated in the groundbreaking ceremony of the HCL-Foxconn Semiconductor Unit in Uttar Pradesh, emphasizing India's move towards technological self-reliance and its growing role in the global chip ecosystem.

Technology.headline: Small Business Technology News: How Will ChatGPT Ads Actually Work?
Technology.detail: OpenAI's head of monetization envisions brands running ad campaigns through ChatGPT by simply conversing with it, potentially reducing costs and technical know-how for small businesses.

Technology.headline: Treasury Unveils Public-Private Initiative to Strengthen Cybersecurity and Risk Management for AI
Technology.detail: The U.S. Department of the Treasury announced a public-private initiative to strengthen cybersecurity and risk management for AI in the financial services sector, releasing a series of six resources developed in partnership with industry and regulators.

Science.headline: “Celtic Curse” Hotspots Found in Scotland and Ireland with 1 in 54 at Risk
Science.detail: Researchers have mapped the genetic risk of hemochromatosis across the UK and Ireland for the first time, uncovering striking hotspots in north-west Ireland and the Outer Hebrides.

Science.headline: Living at High Altitude Protects Against Diabetes
Science.detail: Living at high altitude appears to protect against diabetes, and scientists have finally discovered the reason: When oxygen levels drop, red blood cells switch into a new metabolic mode and absorb large amounts of glucose from the blood.

Science.headline: Ultramarathons May Damage Red Blood Cells and Accelerate Aging
Science.detail: Running extreme distances may strain more than just muscles and joints.

Science.headline: This Extreme Radiation-Resistant Organism Evolved a Remarkable Ability
Science.detail: An organism has evolved a remarkable ability to resist extreme radiation.

Science.headline: Scientists May Have Found The Key Cellular Process Behind Aging in Animals
Science.detail: Scientists are getting closer to understanding the key cellular processes behind aging in animals.

Health.headline: Common bacterium may play surprising role in Alzheimer's disease
Health.detail: Researchers found that Chlamydia pneumoniae can invade the retina and brain, where it sparks inflammation and nerve cell damage, potentially contributing to the development of Alzheimer's. The bacterium is best known for causing pneumonia and sinus infections.

Health.headline: Exercise may sharpen the mind by repairing the brain’s protective shield
Health.detail: Physical activity prompts the liver to release an enzyme that removes a harmful protein causing the blood-brain barrier to become leaky with age. This suggests exercise can help maintain cognitive function by improving the integrity of this protective barrier.

Health.headline: Acalabrutinib + Venetoclax Combo Earns FDA Nod for CLL
Health.detail: The FDA has approved the combination of acalabrutinib and venetoclax for chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL). This provides a new treatment option for patients with this type of cancer.

Health.headline: Parkinson's patients report better balance with Brazilian capoeira dance
Health.detail: Capoeira, a form of martial art disguised as dance, is now being used in Brazil to help patients with Parkinson's disease. The patients say the specific movements of this once-outlawed exercise are improving their physical health.

Health.headline: Protective Clothing, Low-Cost Sunscreens May Cut Expenses
Health.detail: Using protective clothing and low-cost sunscreens can be effective strategies for reducing expenses related to skin cancer prevention. This approach helps minimize the financial burden while still protecting against harmful UV rays.

Sports.headline: Floyd Mayweather returning to pro boxing 9 years after retirement
Sports.detail: The undefeated boxing legend Floyd Mayweather is coming out of retirement after nine years, according to multiple sources.

Sports.headline: NBA: Anthony Edwards fires 40, Wolves hand Mavs 10th straight loss
Sports.detail: Anthony Edwards scored 40 points as the Timberwolves defeated the Mavericks, handing them their 10th straight loss.

Sports.headline: India suffers 0-2 loss to Spain in opening match of Australian leg of FIH Pro League
Sports.detail: India lost to Spain with a score of 0-2 in their opening match of the Australian leg of the FIH Pro League. The match took place on February 21, 2026.

Sports.headline: Harrop, Anselmet combine to win mixed relay for France as part of ski mountaineering's Olympic debut
Sports.detail: France won the mixed relay in ski mountaineering, which is making its debut at the Olympics. Harrop and Anselmet combined to secure the victory for France.

Sports.headline: T20 World Cup: Pakistan opts to bat against New Zealand in Super 8 match, delayed due to rain
Sports.detail: The T20 World Cup Super 8 match between Pakistan and New Zealand has been delayed due to rain. Pakistan has chosen to bat first in the match.

Entertainment.headline: "Jersey Shore" star Nicole "Snooki" Polizzi reveals she has cervical cancer
Entertainment.detail: "Jersey Shore" star Nicole "Snooki" Polizzi said in a TikTok video that her results at a post-op appointment for a cone biopsy showed stage 1 cervical cancer.

Entertainment.headline: KH x RK Reunion: Kamal Haasan-Rajinikanth join hands for Nelson's film; shoot begins soon
Entertainment.detail: Kamal Haasan and Rajinikanth are reportedly collaborating with director Nelson for an upcoming film, with shooting expected to commence shortly.

Entertainment.headline: Marcus Mumford: 'Which living person do I most admire? Sickeningly, it's probably my wife'
Entertainment.detail: Marcus Mumford of Mumford & Sons fame discusses his admiration for his wife in a recent interview.

Entertainment.headline: Hilary Duff on her return to music
Entertainment.detail: Hilary Duff, a Millennial icon, is releasing new music for the first time in over a decade, discussing her return to performing and opening up about relationships in her music.

Entertainment.headline: Eric Dane Friends Launch GoFundMe After Tragic Death
Entertainment.detail: Following the death of actor Eric Dane, friends have started a GoFundMe campaign.

Crime & Justice.headline: Duxbury Mother Faces Court In Triple Murder Case
Crime & Justice.detail: Lindsay Clancy appeared in person at Plymouth Superior Court on February 20, 2026, for the first time since the January 2023 deaths of her three children, with the court hearing focusing on the defense's motion to bifurcate the trial, separating guilt determination from mental health evaluation.

Crime & Justice.headline: Former NFL Player and Laboratory Owner Convicted in $328M Genetic Testing Fraud Scheme
Crime & Justice.detail: A former NFL player and laboratory owner was convicted in a $328 million genetic testing fraud scheme.

Crime & Justice.headline: San Mateo County police reports: Feb. 21, 2026
Crime & Justice.detail: A woman was sitting in her car drinking a bottle of wine on Jefferson Avenue in Redwood City; it was reported 10:08 a.m. Wednesday, Feb. 18.

Crime & Justice.headline: Man arrested after shootout with deputies in north Harris County
Crime & Justice.detail: A man was arrested after a shootout with deputies in north Harris County.

Crime & Justice.headline: Cleveland police: 1 dead, 1 seriously injured after hit-and-run crash on Eddy Road
Crime & Justice.detail: One person is dead and another seriously injured following a hit-and-run crash on Eddy Road in Cleveland.

Education.headline: Whitmer and Michigan Department of Education announce Michigan's high school graduation rate reaches record high
Education.detail: Michigan's 2025 four-year graduation rate has improved to 84%, the highest level since the state adopted the federal formula for calculating the rate in 2008, with the four-year dropout rate improving to 7.1%. Of the largest 20 districts in the state, 16 saw increases in graduation rates.

Education.headline: Pa. needs to adopt new teaching model to curb educator shortage, report finds
Education.detail: A report suggests Pennsylvania needs a more collaborative approach to teaching, allowing teachers to work together, distribute expertise, and have time for professional development during the school day to combat teacher shortages. The proposed model includes differentiated roles and compensation, offering highly effective teachers opportunities to earn more by leading teams or coaching.

Education.headline: Education Briefs Feb. 21
Education.detail: Caitlyn Callahan, of Valdosta, was named to the University of Mississippi's Fall 2025 Honor Roll, which is reserved for students who earn a semester GPA of 3.75-4.00. Kennesaw State University has named more than 6,900 students to the president's list, and congratulates the more than 9,600 students named to the dean's list in recognition of their academic achievement during the Fall 2025 semester.

Education.headline: Springfield School district deadlocked on appointing acting superintendent
Education.detail: The Springfield School District deadlocked on appointing an acting superintendent, caused by discord among school board members, the community, and the district's administration. Applications for the seat close Feb. 27, and the school board is expected to interview finalists March 9.

Education.headline: Schools in England to get budget for children with special needs as part of Send overhaul.
Education.detail: Schools in England will receive a budget for children with special needs as part of an overhaul of the special educational needs and disabilities (SEND) system. Eligibility for special needs support will also be reviewed at the start of secondary school.

Lifestyle.headline: Tesla Cybertruck owner credits FSD for saving life after freeway medical emergency
Lifestyle.detail: A Tesla Cybertruck owner claims that the vehicle's Full Self-Driving (FSD) system saved their life during a medical emergency on the freeway.

Lifestyle.detail: Trader Joe's is recalling over 3 million pounds of products due to potential glass contamination.

Lifestyle.headline: Katseye Says 2026 Is Their Year
Lifestyle.detail: The group Katseye expresses optimism and ambition for the year 2026.

Lifestyle.headline: Sex first, dinner later: what can singles in Oslo, Berlin, Paris and Rome teach me about dating?
Lifestyle.detail: An article explores the dating habits and lessons learned from singles in various European cities.

Lifestyle.headline: Salad praise: how ice hockey's 'lettuce' hair is winning over Hollywood
Lifestyle.detail: A gentler take on mullet has flowed over shoulders at Winter Olympics and is now tossed on red carpets.

Opinion/Editorial.headline: Progressives for news media regulation
Opinion/Editorial.detail: New York legislation would tell publishers how they can and can't use artificial intelligence, potentially hindering their ability to adapt to technological changes.

Opinion/Editorial.headline: Editorial: Why does transparency have to be so partisan?
Opinion/Editorial.detail: The City of Pittsburgh Republican Committee has requested an itemized ledger for $12 million in private donations, which should be standard practice regardless of political affiliations to ensure accountability.

Opinion/Editorial.headline: Editorial: 'Special status' could use scrutiny
Opinion/Editorial.detail: The House and Senate Appropriations committees should examine Secretary Noem's spending and connections to Mr. Lewandowski's private business interests to ensure ethical boundaries are not breached at DHS.

Opinion/Editorial.headline: Daily Editorial Analysis 21 February 2026
Opinion/Editorial.detail: Analysis of key editorials from The Hindu & Indian Express with UPSC-focused insights and relevance, covering topics such as Gen Z's democratic engagement and the importance of 'Bhasha' (language) in education.

World.headline: Trump Announces New 10% Global Tariffs After Supreme Court Rebukes Previous Measures
World.detail: President Donald Trump has imposed a new 10 percent worldwide tariff after the United States Supreme Court struck down his previous trade measures, triggering immediate concern and responses from governments and markets. Trump announced the decision on his social media platform, Truth Social, stating that he signed an executive order to impose the global tariff, which will take effect “almost immediately”.

World.headline: Iran Prepares Nuclear Counterproposal as US Considers Limited Military Strikes
World.detail: Iran's foreign minister expects to have a draft counterproposal ready within days after nuclear talks with the US this week, while Donald Trump said he was considering limited military strikes. The US president has ordered a massive buildup of naval forces in the Middle East, including repositioning aircraft carriers and other warships, leading to fears of an imminent war.

World.headline: Two Soldiers Killed During Military Operation in Pakistan's Northwest: Army
World.detail: Two soldiers were killed during a military operation in Pakistan's northwest. The incident occurred amidst ongoing efforts to combat security threats in the region.

World.headline: 'A Joyful Day': Final Piece of Sagrada Familia's Central Tower Put in Place
World.detail: The final piece of the Sagrada Familia's central tower has been put in place. This marks a significant milestone in the construction of the iconic Barcelona basilica.

World.headline: Kansas Governor Declares State of Emergency Ahead of World Cup
World.detail: Kansas Governor Laura Kelly declared a state of disaster emergency in three counties, anticipating effects from four base camps in the Kansas City-area due to the 2026 North American FIFA World Cup. The influx of an estimated 650,000 visitors to the region is expected to place strain on public safety, emergency and transportation services.

Zimbabwe.headline: KFC, Nando's, and others ditch chicken welfare pledge
Zimbabwe.detail: Several fast-food chains, including KFC and Nando's, have abandoned a commitment to improve chicken welfare standards.

Zimbabwe.headline: Chatunga Mugabe charged with attempted murder for allegedly shooting his gardener
Zimbabwe.detail: Chatunga Mugabe, son of the late former President Robert Mugabe, has been charged with attempted murder after allegedly shooting his gardener in Johannesburg.

Zimbabwe.headline: 40-year-old Zimbabwean man banned from begging in the UK after conviction
Zimbabwe.detail: A 40-year-old Zimbabwean man has been banned from begging in parts of Amesbury, UK, following a conviction.

Zimbabwe.headline: Gray Homes forced to refund US$2800 to Kariba woman who went viral with tearful video
Zimbabwe.detail: Gray Homes has been ordered to refund US$2800 to a Kariba woman after a video of her expressing dissatisfaction went viral.

Zimbabwe.detail: A journalist has been further remanded in custody.
